05:39.311 --> 05:40.914
You're being unreasonable.

05:40.915 --> 05:43.666
- Wait wait, different how?
- Oh, I don't know,

05:43.667 --> 05:46.371
like "I've just been diagnosed
with a life-theatening illness"

05:46.372 --> 05:48.833
"and I want this book to
be my life's last work."

05:49.532 --> 05:51.588
The editor said the book
would be an easier sell

05:51.589 --> 05:53.294
if I included your side of the story,

05:53.295 --> 05:55.071
which I figure benefits you.

05:55.072 --> 05:59.009
- I'm not interested.
- I'm just asking you for a favor.

05:59.010 --> 06:01.308
You want to publish
intimate details about my life

06:01.309 --> 06:02.946
and rehash the choices I've made.

06:02.947 --> 06:05.429
No, you'd be telling your side, not me.

06:05.555 --> 06:08.580
Kathryn, the answer is no.

06:08.581 --> 06:12.596
Ask me tomorrow, ask me next year:
the answer is no.

06:15.643 --> 06:18.582
So since it's mostly a silent film,

06:18.644 --> 06:21.781
we could do something classic
like creepy organ

06:21.898 --> 06:25.222
or something more contemporary suspense,

06:25.223 --> 06:28.097
like some dissonant strings or something.

06:28.445 --> 06:30.188
It's all the same to me,

06:30.420 --> 06:32.172
so I'm gonna have to count on you.

06:32.173 --> 06:34.200
