put it in the box.

20:08.125 --> 20:09.314
I have to make a call.

20:10.952 --> 20:12.752
I don't think he's a morning person.

20:12.992 --> 20:15.853
- That makes two of us.
- Look, I am sorry.

20:15.854 --> 20:17.772
This was the only time he could do this.

20:17.773 --> 20:21.342
And thank you. I know that Angelo
is not your favorite subject.

20:21.606 --> 20:24.435
Yeah, I admit, you know, I'm curious.

20:26.218 --> 20:28.396
What exactly are we looking for?

20:29.382 --> 20:31.437
Anything about the hospital or the switch

20:31.438 --> 20:33.275
or where Angelo might have gone.

20:33.507 --> 20:35.153
Well we know he's not skiing.

20:36.907 --> 20:39.147
Seriously, I never understood
how he ended up in Chicago.

20:39.148 --> 20:41.744
- He hates the cold.
- This is interesting.

20:42.169 --> 20:44.103
- Do you recognize this?
- No.

20:44.640 --> 20:47.209
But then again,
I don't recognize any of this.

20:47.266 --> 20:49.899
I think I have a charger for
this in my junk drawer at home.

20:49.900 --> 20:52.831
I'm going to take it.
Unless of course you want...

20:55.214 --> 20:58.314
- Uh-oh. What is that?
- Maybe he went to see her.

21:00.331 --> 21:03.014
We should probably find out who she is.

21:03.262 --> 21:07.923
You know what? I'll just
deal with this later.

21:11.164 --> 21:13.399
I don't know why I'm so shocked.
It's been 13 years.

21:13.433 --> 21:15.434
Of course he's been with other people.

21:15.469 --> 21:17.536
Yeah, but you don't want to see it.

21:39.190 --> 21:44.049
I never thought that I would say this,
but this is fun.

21:44.049 --> 21:45.498
_

21:45.530 --> 21:49.200
Oh... the grass is wet.
Maybe we should rehearse the next scene.

21:52.470 --> 21:54.222
_

21:57.241 --> 21:58.577
Uh, hey there.

22:01.843 --> 22:03.530
Ha! Hi.

22:03.877 --> 22:06.218
- Hey.
- Thought I would call in the expert

22:06.253 --> 22:07.553
and help us with the camera.

22:07.588 --> 22:10.389
I am sorry that Toby woke you up so early,

22:10.424 --> 22:13.225
- but I'm glad you're here.
- It's not a problem.

22:13.260 --> 22:16.395
Do you know Emmett, my boyfriend?

22:16.429 --> 22:18.597
Emmett, this is Simone. Simone, Emmett.

22:20.977 --> 22:23.101
I think we met at East West, right?

22:26.577 --> 22:29.276
He says it's nice to see you again.

22:30.544 --> 22:31.482
You too.

22:39.188 --> 22:39.786
You know,

22:41.545 --> 22:44.193
a few years ago there were these rumors

22:44.227 --> 22:48.297
about John and this reporter Sarah Lazar.

22:48.880 --> 22:50.466
It didn't really bother me until they...

22:51.601 --> 22:56.138
they ran this picture of them... together.

22:58.793 --> 23:02.242
You know, I actually went
to see a plastic surgeon

23:02.242 --> 23:04.380
because I thought that woutd
give me confidence or something.

23:05.564 --> 23:06.416
It was ridiculous.

23:08.419 --> 23:11.255
I've been the woman trying
to take the guy away.

23:11.289 --> 23:15.193
Trust me... she envied you.

23:15.227 --> 23:18.163
She's writing a book

23:18.197 --> 23:20.132
about the switch.

23:20.166 --> 23:22.100
- You mean us?
- Yeah.

23:22.135 --> 23:24.536
My editor sent me a chapter.

23:25.394 --> 23:27.271
She's writing my story.

23:28.540 --> 23:31.442
I finally understand why
you don't want me to tell yours.

23:32.560 --> 23:36.113
So you're still doing yours?

23:36.564 --> 23:38.415
Yeah.

23:38.852 --> 23:42.108
I have to. It's my life,

23:42.108 --> 23:44.354
and I'm not gonna get
scooped by Sarah Lazar.

23:54.675 --> 23:55.741
Bay.

23:58.446 --> 23:59.501
There you are.

24:01.094 --> 24:03.351
Everyone has been looking for you.

24:04.635 --> 24:05.757
Are you okay?

24:05.757 --> 24:07.489
Let me take a look at that.

24:12.845 --> 24:14.595
And cut!

24:15.610 --> 24:17.004
Oh, mom, seriously,

24:17.004 --> 24:18.632
are you gonna applaud
after every single take?

24:18.667 --> 24:20.634
- You guys are so good.
- Really.

24:20.668 --> 24:22.927
Thanks. I feel like a stiff,

24:22.927 --> 24:25.605
but you are like a total natural.

24:25.639 --> 24:27.740
Yeah, it was super cool. Great job, guys.

24:29.335 --> 24:31.670
_

24:31.746 --> 24:33.781
Um, not too much more though,

24:33.815 --> 24:35.783
'cause otherwise my character

24:35.817 --> 24:38.353
looks dumb for not figuring it out.

24:39.822 --> 24:42.758
- See there, it did it again.
- What's that?

24:42.792 --> 24:45.594
I don't know. Just keeps saying
"Check white balance"

24:45.629 --> 24:46.803
and then it won't record.

24:46.803 --> 24:49.799
Basically it means you gotta
teach the camera what white is.

24:49.833 --> 24:52.164
- How do we do that?
- Teach it to play hacky sack.

24:52.164 --> 24:54.637
- Nice.
- We can try creating a backup file.

24:56.115 --> 24:59.572
Uh, she's saying that
we have a new camera operator.

24:59.572 --> 25:01.597
- That's awesome. Thank you so much.

25:01.597 --> 25:02.608
Ah, here's the foot.

25:02.608 --> 25:05.223
Guys, I could use some help
with the body parts. Thanks.

25:07.434 --> 25:08.535
You're awesome.

25:14.780 --> 25:16.655
I'm trying to. I'm stuck.

25:16.655 --> 25:17.401
_

25:17.401 --> 25:19.413
I don't know what you're saying.

25:19.447 --> 25:20.719
Look, just be cool.

25:21.799 --> 25:23.684
Hey, what's up?

25:23.718 --> 25:26.553
I was just asking some
questions about the script,

25:26.588 --> 25:30.458
- or trying to.
- Yeah, I've been where you are.

25:30.493 --> 25:32.270
Is there anything
you want me to interpret?

25:32.270 --> 25:32.665
_

25:32.665 --> 25:34.142
We don't need to drag you into this.

25:34.142 --> 25:36.699
_

25:36.700 --> 25:37.649
Okay.

25:38.435 --> 25:39.435
Okay.

25:42.573 --> 25:45.509
Mmm, look at that drip.

25:45.937 --> 25:47.544
That's so cool.

25:48.974 --> 25:52.043
The secret ingredient is chocolate sauce.

25:52.132 --> 25:54.587
_

25:55.947 --> 25:58.488
Really? Mmm.

26:02.503 --> 26:05.595
Okay, um, let me check
and I'll call you back.

26:05.930 --> 26:07.330
Okay bye.

26:07.871 --> 26:10.400
That was Geraldo. He's stuck.

26:10.434 --> 26:12.572
One of his hair stylists
for a wedding had to cancel

26:12.572 --> 26:16.440
and he's offering me time
and a half to fill in.

26:16.474 --> 26:18.708
I mean, the hair's basically done here.

26:18.743 --> 26:20.841
And you can do touch-ups, right?

26:20.841 --> 26:21.729
_

26:22.229 --> 26:23.212
I can help.

26:28.486 --> 26:31.621
Do you mind? We could
really use the money.

26:32.086 --> 26:32.915
It's fine.

26:33.582 --> 26:36.345
I'll be back. as soon as I can,

26:36.345 --> 26:38.395
and I'm sure the Kennishes
have got you covered.

26:39.598 --> 26:41.565
- Okay?
- Sure.

26:43.035 --> 26:43.650
Bye.

26:45.261 --> 26:46.198
Bye.

26:55.155 --> 26:58.682
You are a genius! This is perfect, Simone.

26:58.717 --> 27:00.584
Thanks to Mrs. K for the wheels.

27:06.658 --> 27:09.326
Okay, I think I have
the tag line for the poster:

27:09.360 --> 27:12.361
"Dawn of the deaf:
They're silent but deadly."

27:12.909 --> 27:13.990
No.

27:21.270 --> 27:24.472
Hey, so it looks like you've
got a handle on things now,

27:24.507 --> 27:26.574
- and I've got a paper due so...
- What?

27:26.609 --> 27:29.378
No, stay! There's only two more scenes.

27:29.412 --> 27:32.548
Oh my god, you're like
the cutest zombie ever!

27:32.583 --> 27:34.617
Too bad I have to blow your head off.

27:35.753 --> 27:38.721
Okay, you guys are going
to start from out there.

27:39.160 --> 27:42.392
We are going to start on Wilke

27:42.427 --> 27:44.662
and Emmett's going to come up behind him.

27:44.696 --> 27:48.766
Turn away before Emmett has
the chance to bite you.

27:48.800 --> 27:50.867
And then he's gonna cover.

27:50.867 --> 27:51.836
Okay?

27:55.807 --> 27:58.375
- Let's roll it!
- "Dawn of the deaf,"

27:58.409 --> 28:00.310
scene four, take one.

28:01.378 --> 28:02.645
Uh, wait. I don't have a phone.

28:02.679 --> 28:05.414
Uh, here, use this one.

28:05.448 --> 28:07.449
- It really doesn't matter.
- All right.

28:09.619 --> 28:11.654
Okay, let's do it again
from the top.

28:11.688 --> 28:13.756
Scene four, take two.

28:15.759 --> 28:18.261
And, Wilke, start texting.

28:18.295 --> 28:19.596
Action.

28:21.141 --> 28:23.534
Get in closer.

28:23.568 --> 28:26.604
Coming up on Wilke... that's your cue.

28:30.186 --> 28:31.599
Wilke, that's your cue.

28:36.549 --> 28:39.350
Well, cut! Don't look in the camera!

28:42.755 --> 28:44.522
Sorry.

28:44.557 --> 28:47.793
Um, I think I have your phone.

28:49.529 --> 28:51.764
You probably shouldn't
leave it lying around.

28:54.535 --> 28:56.797
All right, let's just try it again.

28:57.651 --> 28:59.705
Back to one.

