33:22.922 --> 33:24.857
Let's go inside. It's so cold, come on.

33:24.891 --> 33:27.959
- Inside!
- Have some cake and some hot chocolate.

33:30.797 --> 33:33.932
- Sweetie, congratulations.
- Thank you.

33:35.079 --> 33:36.063
- I'll see you inside.
- Yeah.

33:36.063 --> 33:37.669
Hey, Wilke, Wilke!

33:38.215 --> 33:39.671
You running off? You should stay.

33:41.359 --> 33:43.675
Sorry, I gotta get home
and do some homework.

33:44.539 --> 33:45.810
Yeah right. Come on, man.

33:46.128 --> 33:48.780
- Simone's blowing it off.
- Yeah well,

33:49.367 --> 33:51.816
Simone can get away with it.

33:52.314 --> 33:53.651
You okay, man?

33:54.067 --> 33:55.653
Yeah, just tired. All right.

33:55.688 --> 33:56.855
I'll catch you later. Okay?

33:56.889 --> 33:57.923
All right.

33:59.692 --> 34:01.593
- What was that?
- Nothing.

34:23.119 --> 34:24.784
I missed everything, didn't I?

34:28.353 --> 34:29.855
It's okay.

34:32.906 --> 34:35.007
I'm sorry. I had to go.

34:36.976 --> 34:38.143
I wish

34:38.178 --> 34:40.367
that I could say no when
work things come up,

34:40.367 --> 34:43.081
- but I can't.
- I get it.

34:45.184 --> 34:46.918
And I know that

34:46.953 --> 34:49.659
I can't give you fog machines

34:49.659 --> 34:52.723
and imported dutch-chocolate blood

34:52.757 --> 34:54.299
and whatever that maze thingy was.

34:54.299 --> 34:58.095
Mom, this isn't about money.

34:58.130 --> 35:00.798
It's not about things. I promise.

35:04.184 --> 35:05.485
Then what is it?

35:08.321 --> 35:10.968
I try not to think about it,

35:10.968 --> 35:14.426
but sometimes I can't help it. It hits me

35:15.115 --> 35:19.398
that there was this whole
childhood I was supposed to have.

35:22.337 --> 35:24.171
I know.

35:24.205 --> 35:28.109
And I'm not saying I didn't
love growing up with you.

35:28.558 --> 35:33.181
You gave me so much and you always
told me I could do anything.

35:33.215 --> 35:36.051
- You can.
- Then why didn't you think

35:36.085 --> 35:38.286
that I could handle
knowing about the switch?

35:39.585 --> 35:41.520
You were three years old.

35:42.522 --> 35:43.688
Okay,

35:43.723 --> 35:45.857
what about when I was five? Or seven?

35:45.891 --> 35:47.792
Or how about when I was 10?

35:50.662 --> 35:53.798
I guess I just...

36:00.191 --> 36:03.093
I didn't think that I could handle it.

36:05.483 --> 36:08.199
I've been trying

36:08.605 --> 36:10.246
to be okay with that,

36:10.569 --> 36:13.238
because I don't want to be
mad at you my whole life.

36:13.549 --> 36:16.809
I hate being mad at you,

36:18.078 --> 36:20.813
but there are so many memories here...

36:20.848 --> 36:24.250
handprints, birdhouses
and family vacations

36:24.284 --> 36:26.252
that I should have been a part of.

36:29.923 --> 36:30.959
I'm sorry.

36:32.926 --> 36:34.827
Me too.

36:42.495 --> 36:45.263
I'm gonna go upstairs.

36:45.297 --> 36:48.970
I think that they're having dessert

36:48.970 --> 36:52.605
and you should join them.

37:16.584 --> 37:17.818
- Hey.
- Hey.

37:18.227 --> 37:20.229
I thought you went to bed.

37:20.263 --> 37:22.097
I thought so too.

37:23.294 --> 37:25.261
Is there any cake left?

37:25.589 --> 37:28.197
No. Oh, but...

37:28.813 --> 37:30.532
You can have one of these. They're yummy.

37:31.511 --> 37:32.634
Zombie fingers.

37:33.276 --> 37:34.637
Oh, okay.

37:36.027 --> 37:39.077
Ugh, tomorrow there is going
to be a massive cleanup

37:39.077 --> 37:41.415
and I am in complete denial.

37:43.491 --> 37:46.104
I meant to say thanks

37:46.104 --> 37:49.156
for letting Daphne take
over your entire home.

37:49.156 --> 37:50.971
Well, it's her home too.

37:52.635 --> 37:54.402
And yours.

37:54.437 --> 37:56.771
I hope you both think of it that way.

37:56.806 --> 37:59.408
Um, I think we're still working on that.

38:00.776 --> 38:03.712
It's crazy sometimes to
think about how we got here.

38:05.368 --> 38:06.911
I think about it all the time.

38:08.252 --> 38:11.155
Maybe I don't think about it enough.

38:11.495 --> 38:14.291
I've gotten pretty good
at denial over the years.

38:17.827 --> 38:18.617
So...

38:20.652 --> 38:24.689
what exactly do you need?
Interviews, notes?

38:24.723 --> 38:27.559
- For what?
- Your book.

38:29.418 --> 38:32.721
I figure if my dirty laundry's
getting aired anyway,

38:32.756 --> 38:34.589
it might as well be you.

38:35.013 --> 38:37.486
- Really?
- One suggestion...

38:38.428 --> 38:41.863
make sure that you take
a really hot author photo,

38:41.863 --> 38:43.565
so Sarah Lazar can suck it.

38:48.471 --> 38:49.871
Was that Regina downstairs?

38:50.263 --> 38:54.409
Yep. She's says she's going to
cooperate with me on my book.

38:54.443 --> 38:56.812
Hey, that's great. What changed her mind?

38:57.164 --> 38:59.748
She wants to help me
kick Sarah Lazar's ass.

39:00.628 --> 39:01.816
You told her about that?

39:02.937 --> 39:05.487
Don't worry. I'm not
gonna put it in the book.

39:06.556 --> 39:08.423
Put what in the book?

39:12.704 --> 39:14.397
I don't feel like talking
about this right now.

39:14.431 --> 39:15.768
I'm exhausted.

39:20.397 --> 39:21.879
You know what, Kathryn?

39:23.208 --> 39:26.177
I really have nothing to
say to you right now.

39:29.133 --> 39:31.168
You don't believe me.

39:31.978 --> 39:33.227
You don't trust me.

39:36.134 --> 39:37.240
Good night.

39:50.769 --> 39:53.104
- Hey, where are you off to?
- I'm just taking Emmett home.

39:53.138 --> 39:54.287
Oh, that's nice.

39:55.975 --> 39:57.876
- Uh, dad?
- Yeah?

39:59.078 --> 40:01.046
Is everything okay with you and mom?

40:01.931 --> 40:04.116
Yeah yeah. Why?

40:06.090 --> 40:09.659
I just felt like something
was going on today.

40:11.062 --> 40:13.697
Well, your mom and I are
going through something,

40:13.731 --> 40:15.732
but it's not really
even worth talking about

40:15.766 --> 40:17.600
because it's going to be fine.

40:17.634 --> 40:18.901
Okay?

40:18.936 --> 40:20.372
We are committed to each other,

40:20.372 --> 40:23.613
and when you're committed,
you work things out.

40:36.074 --> 40:37.374
Hey.

40:39.211 --> 40:41.045
I couldn't sleep.

40:42.181 --> 40:43.281
Me neither.

40:57.969 --> 41:00.362
Are you up for a swim?

41:05.823 --> 41:06.657
Sure.

41:08.630 --> 41:11.109
Maybe we can make some
memories of our own.

41:21.976 --> 41:23.330
Is it cold?

41:23.330 --> 41:24.313
Chicken!

41:24.924 --> 41:27.229
Who are you calling

41:27.229 --> 41:28.193
chicken?

41:29.094 --> 41:30.620
You are such a chicken.

42:10.321 --> 42:13.123
Okay, what is going on?

42:16.293 --> 42:18.995
One minute you're here,
then all of a sudden

42:19.029 --> 42:21.063
you're... I don't know where.

42:21.203 --> 42:22.572
_

42:23.423 --> 42:25.270
_

42:27.103 --> 42:29.221
You hated your birthday. You can say it.

42:29.221 --> 42:32.082
_

42:34.202 --> 42:35.128
_

42:35.278 --> 42:37.079
Then what is it?

42:37.113 --> 42:39.181
We got through the deaf-hearing thing.

42:39.181 --> 42:40.298
We got through the Ty thing.

42:40.298 --> 42:42.297
We got through the custody thing.

42:42.297 --> 42:44.615
We said that we love each other.

42:44.615 --> 42:47.145
What is left for us to get through?

42:49.631 --> 42:50.828
